    "body": "## Updated the complex sqrt function to avoid numerical issues.\r\n\r\nThere are some issues with the current complex sqrt function.\r\n\r\nIt does work not around overflow or underflow, so anywhere `|x|` under/overflows `sqrt` will too, while mathematically all finite values of `x` should lead to finite values of `sqrt(x)`.\r\n\r\nIt also does not account for catastrophic cancellation issues that can arise in normal/non-extremal circumstances, where there can be large accuracy losses.\r\n\r\nFor example, in fp64 we have `sqrt(-1) = 6.123233996e-17 + i`\r\n\r\n\r\nThis new version fixes these accuracy issues, and gives a speedup.\r\n\r\n## Perf\r\nOn all tested systems, H100 and Q8000, CPU, there was speedups.\r\n\r\nUsing the math-teams standard `math_bench` test we have the following on H100 (averaged summary):\r\n**Operations/SM/cycle:**\r\n`csqrt():`\r\n| H100 |  old | new | new/old |\r\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\r\n| fp64 | 0.35614 | 0.94882 | 2.664 | \r\n| fp32 | 0.7396 | 1.78346 | 2.411 |\r\n| half | 0.54516 | 1.62066 | 2.973 |\r\n| bf16 | 0.54958 | 1.58898 | 2.891 |\r\n\r\n(See https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1TdOpEbLgoL1QOWKjeO3pwFDDMoPr4iqnPjz_XrL7UEA for raw/non-averaged info. NV internal.)\r\n\r\n# GPU Correctness\r\nFor the new version, an intensive bracket and bisect search, along with testing special hard values, gives:\r\n```\r\nGPU fp64:\r\nMax ulp real error (3.277,1.172) @ (-1.63385718e+151,-2.682543403e+154) (0xdf53f71f22de2422,0xe000017febfc2db5)\r\n        Ours = (1.157780213e+77,-1.158485597e+77)    Ref = (1.157780213e+77,-1.158485597e+77)\r\n        Ours = (0x4fefff0135f075a6,0xcff001ff60eba13c)               Ref = (0x4fefff0135f075a9,0xcff001ff60eba13b)\r\n\r\nMax ulp imag error (1.154,3.218) @ (7.565676833e+183,5.473795433e+185)  (0x661c7d11e8ada443,0x66801a50ab08f572)\r\n        Ours = (5.267815024e+92,5.195508392e+92)    Ref = (5.267815024e+92,5.195508392e+92)\r\n        Ours = (0x533029a1a415d8b3,0x532fe1acf50ce33d)               Ref = (0x533029a1a415d8b2,0x532fe1acf50ce340)\r\n```\r\n\r\n```\r\nGPU fp32:\r\nMax ulp real error (3.408,0.6557) @ (-1.005818844,2.820671558)  (0xbf80beac,0x403485e2)\r\n        Ours = (0.9972007871,1.414294481)    Ref = (0.9972009659,1.414294362)\r\n        Ours = (0x3f7f488d,0x3fb5079a)               Ref = (0x3f7f4890,0x3fb50799)\r\n\r\nMax ulp imag error (0.9832,3.004) @ (130.0008698,0.04221119359) (0x43020039,0x3d2ce5a5)\r\n        Ours = (11.40179348,0.001851076726)    Ref = (11.40179253,0.001851077075)\r\n        Ours = (0x41366dbf,0x3af29fd4)               Ref = (0x41366dbe,0x3af29fd7)\r\n```\r\n\r\n```\r\nGPU fp16:\r\nMax ulp real error (0.5002,0.02439) @ (-236.625,0.2357177734)   (0xdb65,0x338b)\r\n        Ours = (0.007659912109,15.3828125)    Ref = (0.007663726807,15.3828125)\r\n        Ours = (0x1fd8,0x4bb1)               Ref = (0x1fd9,0x4bb1)\r\n\r\nMax ulp imag error (0.02439,0.5002) @ (946.5,0.9428710938)      (0x6365,0x3b8b)\r\n        Ours = (30.765625,0.01531982422)    Ref = (30.765625,0.01532745361)\r\n        Ours = (0x4fb1,0x23d8)               Ref = (0x4fb1,0x23d9)\r\n```\r\n\r\n```\r\nGPU bf16:\r\nMax ulp real error (0.5,0.3904) @ (-5.757177063e-22,1.043544591e-18)    (0x9c2e,0x219a)\r\n        Ours = (7.203198038e-10,7.239577826e-10)    Ref = (7.239577826e-10,7.239577826e-10)\r\n        Ours = (0x3046,0x3047)               Ref = (0x3047,0x3047)\r\n\r\nMax ulp imag error (0.3904,0.5) @ (4.670776934e+10,8.466239534e+13)     (0x512e,0x569a)\r\n        Ours = (6520832,6488064)    Ref = (6520832,6520832)\r\n        Ours = (0x4ac7,0x4ac6)               Ref = (0x4ac7,0x4ac7)\r\n```\r\n\r\n# CPU Correctness\r\n```\r\nCPU fp64:\r\nMax ulp real error (2.891,0.9599) @ (-2.898436088e-156,5.954779844e-154)        (0x9fa3e5ad68e29000,0x201fefabf7a5a200)\r\n        Ours = (1.721317231e-77,1.72971598e-77)    Ref = (1.721317231e-77,1.72971598e-77)\r\n        Ours = (0x2fffe3f0663c7eb6,0x300005e2f2271e6e)               Ref = (0x2fffe3f0663c7eb9,0x300005e2f2271e6d)\r\n\r\nMax ulp imag error (1.035,2.782) @ (8.841641372e-291,1.314161111e-287)  (0x3b60ee1a0d83b80,0x4600236498008c0)\r\n        Ours = (2.564220712e-144,2.562496092e-144)    Ref = (2.564220712e-144,2.562496092e-144)\r\n        Ours = (0x2220027bffde5d7b,0x221fff74a8e61bab)               Ref = (0x2220027bffde5d7c,0x221fff74a8e61ba8)\r\n```\r\n\r\n```\r\nCPU fp32:\r\nMax ulp real error (3.21,1.201) @ (-0.03916323557,-2.006309986) (0xbd2069a1,0xc0006762)\r\n        Ours = (0.9918488264,-1.011399031)    Ref = (0.9918490052,-1.011398911)\r\n        Ours = (0x3f7de9ce,0xbf817586)               Ref = (0x3f7de9d1,0xbf817585)\r\n\r\nMax ulp imag error (1.126,3.19) @ (0.03352772817,-2.02899766)   (0x3d09545f,0xc001db19)\r\n        Ours = (1.015579104,-0.9989363551)    Ref = (1.015579224,-0.9989361763)\r\n        Ours = (0x3f81fe7f,0xbf7fba4b)               Ref = (0x3f81fe80,0xbf7fba48)\r\n```\r\n\r\n```\r\nCPU fp16:\r\nMax ulp real error (0.5002,0.09433) @ (-65.75,0.05352783203)    (0xd41c,0x2ada)\r\n        Ours = (0.003299713135,8.109375)    Ref = (0.003301620483,8.109375)\r\n        Ours = (0x1ac2,0x480e)               Ref = (0x1ac3,0x480e)\r\n\r\nMax ulp imag error (0.09433,0.5002) @ (0.06420898438,5.227327347e-05)   (0x2c1c,0x36d)\r\n        Ours = (0.2534179688,0.0001031160355)    Ref = (0.2534179688,0.0001031756401)\r\n        Ours = (0x340e,0x6c2)               Ref = (0x340e,0x6c3)\r\n```\r\n\r\n```\r\nCPU bf16: \r\nMax ulp real error (0.5,0.4948) @ (-2.11312391e+12,1.068373115e+11)     (0xd3f6,0x51c7)\r\n        Ours = (36864,1458176)    Ref = (36608,1458176)\r\n        Ours = (0x4710,0x49b2)               Ref = (0x470f,0x49b2)\r\n\r\nMax ulp imag error (0.4948,0.5) @ (3.380998255e+13,-1.709396984e+12)    (0x55f6,0xd3c7)\r\n        Ours = (5832704,-147456)    Ref = (5832704,-146432)\r\n        Ours = (0x4ab2,0xc810)               Ref = (0x4ab2,0xc80f)\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Note on `rsqrt`:\r\nWithin this new implementation we at some point calculate `1.0/sqrt(x)`.\r\nIn CUDA, on device, we have math functions for this, `rsqrtf` for fp32 and `rsqrt` for fp64.\r\n\r\nWhile I found the algorithm got faster using `rsqrtf` for fp32, using `rsqrt` for fp64 resulted in a small slowdown, surprisingly to me (on both tested systems).\r\n\r\nMy working hypothesis is that while `rsqrtf` maps to a single CUDA asm instruction, `rsqrt` gets mapped to an llvm-ir intrinsic.\r\nI haven't investigated fully yet, but it seems the compiler has some better tricks than I for optimizing `1/sqrt(x)`.",
